WEBVTT

1
00:00:10.010 --> 00:00:11.302
[marker scribbles]

2
00:00:17.017 --> 00:00:18.268
[Isla] Where were we?

3
00:00:18.351 --> 00:00:20.145
[percussive music playing]

4
00:00:21.146 --> 00:00:22.313
Hey. what's up. sis?

5
00:00:22.397 --> 00:00:23.648
[Isla] Oh right.

6
00:00:23.732 --> 00:00:24.941
I'm back.

7
00:00:25.025 --> 00:00:28.570
[Isla] Cam Gordon. oldest brother.
former president of the LA Waves.

8
00:00:28.653 --> 00:00:30.321
He gave me this job. and I love him.

9
00:00:30.405 --> 00:00:33.074
but his junkie ass is
supposed to be in rehab.

10
00:00:33.158 --> 00:00:34.409
What the actual hell?

11
00:00:35.118 --> 00:00:37.662
Cam. Oh my God!

12
00:00:37.746 --> 00:00:40.165
-[Cam] Oh.
-[Isla] Hi. Oh!

13
00:00:40.248 --> 00:00:41.541
Oh. I miss hugs.

14
00:00:41.624 --> 00:00:42.542
[both] Mm.

15
00:00:42.625 --> 00:00:44.502
My parole officers were never this good.

16
00:00:44.586 --> 00:00:49.966
I watched the game last night.
We almost had 'em. but… tough loss.

17
00:00:50.050 --> 00:00:52.886
[inhales deeply] Th-- Thanks.
Yeah. I'm still in shock.

18
00:00:53.386 --> 00:00:57.015
So. when you say back.

19
00:00:57.724 --> 00:01:01.978
you mean back like as in a limited time.
like the McRib.

20
00:01:02.062 --> 00:01:04.105
or back. like. for your job?

21
00:01:04.189 --> 00:01:08.193
Oh God. no. no. no. no. no.
You are the president of the Waves.

22
00:01:08.276 --> 00:01:10.445
Me? I'm just a guy
who just got out of rehab.

23
00:01:10.528 --> 00:01:12.405
But now that you mention it.

24
00:01:12.489 --> 00:01:14.699
I… I would like to come back
and work just a little bit.

25
00:01:14.783 --> 00:01:15.950
you know. just to help out.

26
00:01:16.034 --> 00:01:17.911
Oh. well. what… what do I need help with?

27
00:01:17.994 --> 00:01:20.330
I can consult if you have any questions.

28
00:01:20.413 --> 00:01:22.624
or maybe you give me
a little bit of an office.

29
00:01:22.707 --> 00:01:24.209
-[Isla] Mmm.
-I can do the Oscar pool.

30
00:01:24.292 --> 00:01:25.710
Oh. come on. Cam.

31
00:01:25.794 --> 00:01:28.379
-You know Sandy runs the Oscar pool.
-Oh. right.

32
00:01:28.463 --> 00:01:31.925
-You're not gunning for your old job back?
-Oh my God. no.

33
00:01:32.008 --> 00:01:34.094
Besides. you're doing such a great job.

34
00:01:34.177 --> 00:01:36.346
and the board would
never even approve me at this point.

35
00:01:36.429 --> 00:01:38.139
Not with my rap sheet.

36
00:01:38.223 --> 00:01:40.475
-Oh. sorry. Old habits die hard.
-[chuckles]

37
00:01:40.558 --> 00:01:42.560
And you're okay working under me?

38
00:01:42.644 --> 00:01:46.564
Yes. Look. I'm a different person now.
I listen.

39
00:01:46.648 --> 00:01:48.900
Lizzie told me something
about the kids the other day.

40
00:01:48.983 --> 00:01:50.443
and I heard it. I really heard it.

41
00:01:50.527 --> 00:01:52.112
Apparently we got a bed wetter.

42
00:01:52.195 --> 00:01:53.113
[tapping on door]

43
00:01:53.196 --> 00:01:56.324
Just. uh. checking to see
if you needed anything?

44
00:01:56.866 --> 00:01:57.992
-Jason.
-Jackie.

45
00:01:58.076 --> 00:02:01.287
Jack-- Jackie. I wanna apologize
for getting off on the wrong foot.

46
00:02:01.371 --> 00:02:03.748
I've had eight months.
and I've really learned a lot.

47
00:02:03.832 --> 00:02:06.334
-I want to get to know you better.
-Thank you. Cam.

48
00:02:06.417 --> 00:02:07.377
Hey. no problem.

49
00:02:07.460 --> 00:02:11.047
Oh. and if you're going on a coffee run.
I would love a caramel macchiato.

50
00:02:11.131 --> 00:02:12.173
Oh my God.

51
00:02:12.257 --> 00:02:14.467
Oh. there he is. My man.

52
00:02:14.551 --> 00:02:16.261
[both grunting]

53
00:02:16.344 --> 00:02:18.263
I thought the court said
you had to do a full year.

54
00:02:18.346 --> 00:02:21.307
No. the rehab wrote the judge a letter.
and they let me out early.

55
00:02:21.391 --> 00:02:23.434
-Well. I'm proud of you. man.
-Oh. thanks.

56
00:02:23.518 --> 00:02:24.978
I can't believe this is the same guy

57
00:02:25.061 --> 00:02:27.856
that Bituin caught going through her purse
looking for opioids.

58
00:02:27.939 --> 00:02:29.941
-[laughing]
-I was a wild man.

59
00:02:30.024 --> 00:02:31.109
Now you can be in book club.

60
00:02:31.192 --> 00:02:33.444
I know before you said
book clubs were for pussies.

61
00:02:33.528 --> 00:02:34.779
But now I know you were high.

62
00:02:34.863 --> 00:02:37.740
Right. No. I would love
to be part of the book club.

63
00:02:37.824 --> 00:02:38.825
Yeah. come on by.

64
00:02:38.908 --> 00:02:41.077
Hey. so what's going on? Are… are you…?

65
00:02:41.661 --> 00:02:44.205
-You're back-back?
-[Cam] Well. that's up to Isla.

66
00:02:46.416 --> 00:02:47.375
What do you say?

67
00:02:47.458 --> 00:02:49.002
[tense music playing]

68
00:02:51.379 --> 00:02:52.797
We'd be lucky to have you back.

69
00:02:52.881 --> 00:02:55.884
-Yes! Yes! Yes! We should celebrate.
-[Cam laughs]

70
00:02:55.967 --> 00:02:58.678
-Champagne. Yes!
-Oh. I don't think that'd be a great idea.

71
00:02:58.761 --> 00:03:00.805
-[Ness] No. No champagne.
-Let's go get a Coke.

72
00:03:00.889 --> 00:03:03.349
Hey. I need a new office. don't I?

73
00:03:03.433 --> 00:03:05.518
[upbeat music playing]

74
00:03:05.602 --> 00:03:07.395
[Isla] So I guess Cam's back.

75
00:03:08.229 --> 00:03:09.647
♪ You better watch out ♪

76
00:03:09.731 --> 00:03:11.900
♪ If you wanna survive ♪

77
00:03:11.983 --> 00:03:15.403
♪ Listen to me or just step aside ♪

78
00:03:16.738 --> 00:03:18.656
[footsteps]

79
00:03:18.740 --> 00:03:20.742
[upbeat music fades]

80
00:03:22.202 --> 00:03:23.411
[sentimental music playing]

81
00:03:23.494 --> 00:03:24.537
[Isla sighs deeply]

82
00:03:27.373 --> 00:03:28.291
[clicks tongue]

83
00:03:32.212 --> 00:03:34.422
-[sighs]
-I didn't take you for sentimental.

84
00:03:34.505 --> 00:03:36.716
Oh my God. Jay. I…

85
00:03:38.426 --> 00:03:41.512
-I thought you were already in Boston.
-Yeah. I uh… I leave tonight.

86
00:03:42.513 --> 00:03:45.934
I just… just needed to do one more thing.

87
00:03:49.020 --> 00:03:51.022
[romantic music playing]

88
00:03:53.608 --> 00:03:55.235
[Isla moans]

89
00:03:55.318 --> 00:03:57.445
[books falling off desk]

90
00:03:58.029 --> 00:04:00.365
Mm. I put flaxseeds in your smoothie.

91
00:04:02.492 --> 00:04:03.785
-What?
-[kissing]

92
00:04:03.868 --> 00:04:06.454
The Mayo Clinic recommends
one scoop a day.

93
00:04:06.537 --> 00:04:08.331
Helps support healthy elimination.

94
00:04:08.414 --> 00:04:10.333
-[Isla gasps] Whoa.
-Whoa.

95
00:04:10.416 --> 00:04:13.461
Have you been sleeping this whole time?
You were smiling and nodding.

96
00:04:13.544 --> 00:04:15.046
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

97
00:04:15.129 --> 00:04:17.382
I made you this.
It's got all your daily nutrients.

98
00:04:17.465 --> 00:04:20.510
So the rest of the day.
you can just have Diet Coke and Skittles.

99
00:04:20.593 --> 00:04:23.221
But when we get married.
this has gotta stop.

100
00:04:23.304 --> 00:04:26.683
-I don't wanna be a widower in my forties.
-Please. women will be lining up.

101
00:04:26.766 --> 00:04:29.894
You're gonna be remarried
before they're finished with my autopsy.

102
00:04:29.978 --> 00:04:31.187
All right. I gotta go.

103
00:04:31.271 --> 00:04:32.397
[kissing]

104
00:04:32.480 --> 00:04:35.900
[Isla] Damn. that's the fifth fantasy
I've had about Jay this week.

105
00:04:37.068 --> 00:04:39.362
[sighs] Ever since Jay and I kissed
after the playoffs.

106
00:04:39.445 --> 00:04:41.364
I've been having
nonstop sex dreams about him.

107
00:04:41.447 --> 00:04:42.365
I'm talking at work.

108
00:04:43.074 --> 00:04:44.492
Like. all over work.

109
00:04:44.575 --> 00:04:49.163
Even on Planet Arrakis.
I think I fell asleep watching Dune.

110
00:04:49.247 --> 00:04:51.332
I don't know how. but I need them to stop

111
00:04:51.416 --> 00:04:53.960
because Lev and I are back together
and have never been better.

112
00:04:54.043 --> 00:04:55.503
and we actually set a date.

113
00:04:55.586 --> 00:04:57.630
[chuckles] That's right.

114
00:04:57.714 --> 00:05:00.133
Your girl is getting married
in just eight short weeks

115
00:05:00.216 --> 00:05:01.884
to the man of her dreams.

116
00:05:01.968 --> 00:05:04.053
[Isla] Well. most of my dreams.

117
00:05:04.137 --> 00:05:06.472
Yeah. let's keep it going!
Come on! Who wants it?

118
00:05:06.556 --> 00:05:07.473
Come on! Who wants it?

119
00:05:08.766 --> 00:05:10.351
To the line! To the line…

120
00:05:10.435 --> 00:05:13.271
[Isla] Work has been surprisingly great
with Cam back.

121
00:05:13.354 --> 00:05:15.398
He's been really helpful and supportive.

122
00:05:16.065 --> 00:05:19.569
The team has been crushing
their off-season workouts.

123
00:05:19.652 --> 00:05:21.904
They're still pissed about
how last season ended. which is good.

124
00:05:21.988 --> 00:05:24.824
because this year.
I plan on winning it all.

125
00:05:25.533 --> 00:05:29.454
If you want a legacy in this league.
you can't be a one-hit wonder.

126
00:05:29.537 --> 00:05:30.621
Dad would be so proud

127
00:05:30.705 --> 00:05:34.834
that his five children. that we know of.
are working under one roof.

128
00:05:34.917 --> 00:05:38.296
We still need a coach.
but I am on top of it.

129
00:05:38.379 --> 00:05:39.756
Sure. it's been a few months.

130
00:05:39.839 --> 00:05:42.216
and none of the candidates
have blown me away yet.

131
00:05:42.300 --> 00:05:44.052
but I know I'll find the right guy.

132
00:05:44.135 --> 00:05:46.846
-It's just taking me a minute to--
-I think I found our guy.

133
00:05:46.929 --> 00:05:49.265
-Danny Pierce.
-Coach from Oklahoma?

134
00:05:49.349 --> 00:05:51.100
Oh. he's tied up at OU.

135
00:05:51.184 --> 00:05:54.354
Yeah. I bumped into him in Malibu.
We ended up going to the Soho Beach House.

136
00:05:54.437 --> 00:05:58.066
I think he's up here visiting his aunt.
who's like Jamie Lee Curtis or some shit.

137
00:05:58.149 --> 00:06:00.860
I love Freaky Friday.
They should make more body swap movies.

138
00:06:00.943 --> 00:06:02.779
-I'm always saying that.
-They make plenty.

139
00:06:03.946 --> 00:06:04.864
[Cam] There's my guy.

140
00:06:04.947 --> 00:06:05.782
[sighs] Yeah. I know.

141
00:06:05.865 --> 00:06:08.284
I got the feeling if we made him an offer.
he'd be interested.

142
00:06:08.993 --> 00:06:11.954
-Well. we should interview him.
-[Cam] Totally.

143
00:06:12.038 --> 00:06:13.956
Of course.
he'd be interviewing us as well.

144
00:06:14.040 --> 00:06:14.957
[scoffs] Excuse me?

145
00:06:15.041 --> 00:06:18.086
No. no. I get that.
I mean. this guy is a god at OU.

146
00:06:18.169 --> 00:06:20.880
He can park his golf cart anywhere.
Why would he ever leave?

147
00:06:20.963 --> 00:06:23.716
Uh. to coach the most famous
professional basketball team in the world?

148
00:06:23.800 --> 00:06:27.220
Yeah. Run by
a very savvy and innovative leader.

149
00:06:27.303 --> 00:06:28.638
-[Isla grunts]
-Oh!

150
00:06:28.721 --> 00:06:29.972
These are bad chairs.

151
00:06:30.056 --> 00:06:31.557
Isla. of course. it's up to you.

152
00:06:31.641 --> 00:06:33.768
but I think we should. uh.
ask him to sit with us.

153
00:06:33.851 --> 00:06:35.561
-I agree.
-All right.

154
00:06:35.645 --> 00:06:38.606
Uh… Jackie. set up a meeting.

155
00:06:38.689 --> 00:06:40.983
Oh! No need to do that.
I just got off the phone with him.

156
00:06:41.067 --> 00:06:44.112
Told him to come around here
this afternoon. Just faster that way.

157
00:06:44.195 --> 00:06:45.696
-[Ness] Boom.
-Great.

158
00:06:46.656 --> 00:06:49.450
Why is there a framed photo
of some random child here?

159
00:06:49.534 --> 00:06:51.536
That is my son. Milton.

160
00:06:51.619 --> 00:06:52.870
Isla gave Cam my office.

161
00:06:52.954 --> 00:06:55.206
So. now this conference room
has become my workstation.

162
00:06:55.289 --> 00:06:58.251
Oh. you know what? Maybe if I go to rehab.
Isla will give me Sandy's office.

163
00:06:58.334 --> 00:06:59.335
Oh. boo-hoo-hoo.

164
00:06:59.419 --> 00:07:01.421
It's not exactly paradise
over in your office.

165
00:07:01.504 --> 00:07:03.172
It's like fucking Anthropologie
over there.

166
00:07:03.256 --> 00:07:05.800
-Then give it back. bitch.
-Who the fuck you calling "bitch." bitch?

167
00:07:05.883 --> 00:07:09.804
Hey. nobody says bitch here
unless it's in a fun and sassy gay way.

168
00:07:09.887 --> 00:07:11.305
Right. Sandy?

169
00:07:11.389 --> 00:07:14.267
I wish I was sassy.
but I'm not that type of gay.

170
00:07:15.143 --> 00:07:18.396
Isla. you know how many years
it took me to earn my office?

171
00:07:18.479 --> 00:07:21.315
Your dad gave it to me on his deathbed.
He was on so much tramadol.

172
00:07:21.399 --> 00:07:22.233
He was nice for once.

173
00:07:22.316 --> 00:07:24.277
Okay. I promise
I'm gonna find you an office.

174
00:07:24.360 --> 00:07:25.278
[softly] Thank you.

175
00:07:25.361 --> 00:07:26.529
[gentle music playing]

176
00:07:27.613 --> 00:07:29.407
It's come to my attention

177
00:07:29.490 --> 00:07:33.035
that none of y'all ain't bought a table
for the Complexion Ball.

178
00:07:33.661 --> 00:07:36.706
-What is the Complexion Ball again?
-How many times do we have to tell you?

179
00:07:36.789 --> 00:07:40.710
It's for his wife Dinora's charity
to eradicate cystic acne.

180
00:07:40.793 --> 00:07:43.045
Damn. Travis. that's…
that's exactly right.

181
00:07:43.129 --> 00:07:45.506
Key to staying sharp. sober living.

182
00:07:45.590 --> 00:07:47.133
and app-based brain games.

183
00:07:47.216 --> 00:07:49.177
Today's Wordle. tough.

184
00:07:49.260 --> 00:07:51.304
-Dude. they're always tough. Benson.
-[Benson sighs]

185
00:07:51.387 --> 00:07:54.849
The table buy-in is 10.000.
and you're all getting one.

186
00:07:54.932 --> 00:07:56.017
[murmuring]

187
00:07:56.100 --> 00:07:58.686
Yo. Marcus. I'm sorry.
but I can't make the pimple party. man.

188
00:07:58.769 --> 00:08:01.939
My. uh. grandma needs help
setting up her iPad.

189
00:08:02.732 --> 00:08:04.859
Don't lie to me.
Look. you don't have to buy a table.

190
00:08:04.942 --> 00:08:07.445
but you are coming
and you are walking the rosacea carpet.

191
00:08:07.528 --> 00:08:08.404
All right. fine.

192
00:08:08.488 --> 00:08:10.781
And don't be wearing
that busted-ass corduroy suit.

193
00:08:10.865 --> 00:08:13.618
-Looking like a Jehovah's Witness.
-I am a Jehovah's Witness.

194
00:08:14.702 --> 00:08:17.205
Goddammit. We going shopping.

195
00:08:17.288 --> 00:08:19.665
[gentle music playing]

196
00:08:19.749 --> 00:08:22.293
All right. look.
obviously when I take over.

197
00:08:22.376 --> 00:08:23.920
I'm gonna need to make my adjustments.

198
00:08:24.003 --> 00:08:27.423
It's all about maximizing everyone's
player efficiency rating and our EFG.

199
00:08:27.507 --> 00:08:28.674
That's right.

200
00:08:28.758 --> 00:08:32.303
-That's expected field goal percentage.
-Oh God. you have hot tuna breath.

201
00:08:32.386 --> 00:08:36.516
We definitely gotta lose the zone defense.
Man-to-man. all the time.

202
00:08:36.599 --> 00:08:37.850
My teams do not rest.

203
00:08:37.934 --> 00:08:40.228
-Oh. I love that.
-Fuck yeah. that's what I'm talking about.

204
00:08:40.311 --> 00:08:43.940
I like that in theory. but we really try
to keep Marcus's wear and tear down

205
00:08:44.023 --> 00:08:45.274
in the regular season.

206
00:08:45.358 --> 00:08:47.902
But we also like that you're coming
in here with all these ideas.

207
00:08:47.985 --> 00:08:51.030
Oh. thanks. Listen. when you hire me.
you don't just get the coach.

208
00:08:51.113 --> 00:08:53.574
You also get the president and the GM.
Pew. pew. pew.

209
00:08:53.658 --> 00:08:55.743
[laughs] I can wear a lot of hats
is what I'm saying.

210
00:08:55.826 --> 00:08:57.870
Not that you should
with that head of lettuce.

211
00:08:57.954 --> 00:08:59.455
-Oh. okay.
-[chuckles]

212
00:08:59.539 --> 00:09:00.581
Listen. I gotta get going.

213
00:09:00.665 --> 00:09:03.709
I'm doing a photo shoot for Men's Health.
I guess it's the abs issue.

214
00:09:03.793 --> 00:09:06.546
-Oh shit. I'll walk you out.
-Thank you so much. Thank you.

215
00:09:06.629 --> 00:09:07.880
I'm actually gonna come with you

216
00:09:07.964 --> 00:09:10.258
'cause I wanna get
your thoughts on oblique training.

217
00:09:10.925 --> 00:09:14.345
Well. I like him. I guess I'm about to go
to a magazine stand for the first time.

218
00:09:14.428 --> 00:09:17.807
This is why we pay
for Cam's many social club memberships.

219
00:09:18.391 --> 00:09:19.392
Isla.

220
00:09:19.475 --> 00:09:21.561
[party music playing]

221
00:09:22.603 --> 00:09:25.815
[engine whirring]

222
00:09:27.441 --> 00:09:28.276
[car door closes]

223
00:09:28.359 --> 00:09:30.361
[indistinct chatter]

224
00:09:30.444 --> 00:09:32.905
I… I think you're prematurely cheesing.
I'm just gonna say it.

225
00:09:32.989 --> 00:09:35.700
You're gonna get about 15% more
grill space on your lower right

226
00:09:35.783 --> 00:09:36.617
if you shift every--

227
00:09:36.701 --> 00:09:38.869
Here you go. I know you want it.
I know you want it.

228
00:09:38.953 --> 00:09:40.371
-Go for it.
-I'm just gonna do it.

229
00:09:40.454 --> 00:09:43.291
No. Lev. where you going? Right there.
I'm done. I'm done.

230
00:09:43.374 --> 00:09:45.084
They have to get their swim diapers on.

231
00:09:45.167 --> 00:09:47.628
Thank you for letting me bring my mom
so she can watch the kids.

232
00:09:47.712 --> 00:09:48.879
Where's Gene?

233
00:09:48.963 --> 00:09:50.923
He's taking a stand-up class at Flappers.

234
00:09:51.007 --> 00:09:53.426
-Oh. okay.
-I know.

235
00:09:53.509 --> 00:09:56.012
Um. hey. there's actually something
I wanted to talk to you about.

236
00:09:56.095 --> 00:09:57.179
[gasps] Oh.

237
00:09:57.263 --> 00:09:58.556
[sighs] Cam's office.

238
00:09:58.639 --> 00:10:00.808
I'm sorry.
I forgot with all the coach stuff.

239
00:10:00.891 --> 00:10:02.059
No. no. no. It's… it's fine.

240
00:10:02.143 --> 00:10:05.271
There's actually something bigger
I wanted to run by you. Um…

241
00:10:05.354 --> 00:10:10.109
[inhales sharply] There is a song
called "Flowers" by Miley Cyrus.

242
00:10:10.192 --> 00:10:11.902
It's about knowing your self-worth.

243
00:10:11.986 --> 00:10:15.197
-And as you know--
-What is this? Are you nervous?

244
00:10:15.281 --> 00:10:17.783
Spit it out.
I've got 80 crab cakes in the oven.

245
00:10:17.867 --> 00:10:18.743
Okay. fine.

246
00:10:18.826 --> 00:10:20.745
Look. it's awkward
because you're my best friend.

247
00:10:20.828 --> 00:10:23.789
but you're also my boss.
and I… I just have to say it.

248
00:10:24.832 --> 00:10:26.542
I think I deserve a raise.

249
00:10:26.626 --> 00:10:28.544
Wow. okay. I…

250
00:10:28.628 --> 00:10:31.714
You know. when Cam left. you stepped up.
but… but I stepped up too.

251
00:10:31.797 --> 00:10:34.717
And I love all my new responsibilities.
but I just really feel like--

252
00:10:34.800 --> 00:10:37.011
You're so right. You need a raise.

253
00:10:37.511 --> 00:10:40.806
And I'm gonna talk to Sandy about it.
I'm gonna make it my priority. I'm on it.

254
00:10:40.890 --> 00:10:42.725
Oh my God. Oh. thank you so much.

255
00:10:42.808 --> 00:10:46.270
This just means so much to me. especially
with Gene wanting to quit dentistry

256
00:10:46.354 --> 00:10:47.647
to pursue comedy full-time.

257
00:10:47.730 --> 00:10:51.067
-Hmm. Never made me laugh.
-He's never made anyone laugh.

258
00:10:51.692 --> 00:10:52.818
-[Isla] Hey. Cam.
-Hey.

259
00:10:52.902 --> 00:10:54.111
[Isla] Oh. uh. sorry.

260
00:10:54.195 --> 00:10:57.615
Hi. the clogged toilet is upstairs. Ness.

261
00:10:57.698 --> 00:10:58.866
What?

262
00:10:58.949 --> 00:11:02.536
Hey. he's not the fucking plumber.
This is my sober companion. Leroy.

263
00:11:02.620 --> 00:11:03.663
-[Leroy] Hey.
-Oh.

264
00:11:03.746 --> 00:11:05.623
[Isla] Sorry. Good to meet you.

265
00:11:05.706 --> 00:11:08.834
Oh shit. you got a pool?
Could I borrow a bathing suit?

266
00:11:08.918 --> 00:11:10.378
Oh. I… I don't think we have any.

267
00:11:10.461 --> 00:11:13.422
Actually. you know what? I'm cool.
I can wear my tighty-whities.

268
00:11:13.506 --> 00:11:15.007
Oh. Uh… Hey. oh. Lev.

269
00:11:15.091 --> 00:11:18.928
Leroy here needs a bathing suit.
Do you have an extra one for him. please?

270
00:11:19.011 --> 00:11:19.970
Of course. You got it.

271
00:11:20.471 --> 00:11:21.430
Oh. Ooh.

272
00:11:21.514 --> 00:11:24.058
Hey. Leroy.
Yeah. I have a bathing suit for you.

273
00:11:24.141 --> 00:11:26.227
-You know. you can… you can keep it.
-What?

274
00:11:26.310 --> 00:11:28.938
Feel free to hop in the outdoor shower
before you jump in.

275
00:11:29.021 --> 00:11:30.564
What's up with the indoor shower though?

276
00:11:31.232 --> 00:11:32.733
That guy's amazing. He saved my life.

277
00:11:34.485 --> 00:11:35.611
[Cam exhales]

278
00:11:35.695 --> 00:11:37.822
You put him on every billboard in LA?

279
00:11:37.905 --> 00:11:40.074
[exhales deeply] I mean.
that's expansive outreach.

280
00:11:40.157 --> 00:11:44.120
-Are you still talking about Danny?
-Yeah. The offer will be ready on Monday.

281
00:11:44.203 --> 00:11:47.581
-Let's get it out as soon as possible.
-Great. I'll do that. Right?

282
00:11:47.665 --> 00:11:50.042
Oh. right.
that's if it's okay with you. boss.

283
00:11:50.126 --> 00:11:52.461
Yeah. Send it to me first.
and I'll take a look at it.

284
00:11:52.545 --> 00:11:54.630
I'd love to get
a text chain going with him.

285
00:11:54.714 --> 00:11:56.674
-Easy. I'll put us on a group chat.
-I love it.

286
00:11:56.757 --> 00:11:58.300
Hello. Okay. What about me?

287
00:11:58.384 --> 00:11:59.510
Danny's cool.

288
00:11:59.593 --> 00:12:02.346
-I wanna be on the chain.
-Oh. we never forget about you.

289
00:12:02.430 --> 00:12:04.765
-You're our guy. The ultimate cool guy.
-No. no. no.

290
00:12:04.849 --> 00:12:07.226
Don't Gladiator me. please.
Guys. our backs are turned.

291
00:12:07.309 --> 00:12:10.146
-Are you not entertained?
-Don't. please. No. No. no. no. no!

292
00:12:10.730 --> 00:12:11.772
[child laughs]

293
00:12:11.856 --> 00:12:13.023
Whoo!

294
00:12:13.107 --> 00:12:14.775
-Whoo!
-Oh!

295
00:12:15.693 --> 00:12:17.403
[Jackie] Can I be honest with you?

296
00:12:17.486 --> 00:12:19.780
I'm not there on this Danny thing.

297
00:12:19.864 --> 00:12:23.701
Well. on paper. he checks all the boxes.
and he's the hottest coach available.

298
00:12:23.784 --> 00:12:24.910
But. I mean. still your call.

299
00:12:24.994 --> 00:12:29.165
Isn't it weird
that he's. like. already Cam's guy?

300
00:12:29.248 --> 00:12:30.082
[Ali sighs]

301
00:12:30.166 --> 00:12:32.501
And he wants to change
everything we've built.

302
00:12:32.585 --> 00:12:34.962
Well. I mean. you just had
to be a decent human being

303
00:12:35.045 --> 00:12:37.298
and let Jay be with his children. [scoffs]

304
00:12:37.798 --> 00:12:40.050
Jay's like an extension of our family.

305
00:12:40.134 --> 00:12:43.429
I mean. he was a player
and then assistant. head coach.

306
00:12:43.512 --> 00:12:46.307
I just need someone
who understands this organization.

307
00:12:47.057 --> 00:12:49.226
Well. the head coach before Jay
was Bruce Adams.

308
00:12:49.310 --> 00:12:50.978
but he's dead. so that's a no-go.

309
00:12:51.061 --> 00:12:54.190
Jay always said
his real mentor was Norm Stinson.

310
00:12:54.273 --> 00:12:55.816
[gasps] Wait.

311
00:12:56.484 --> 00:12:57.485
What ever happened to him?

312
00:12:57.568 --> 00:12:59.945
After he won a title
as an assistant coach for your dad.

313
00:13:00.029 --> 00:13:02.448
he was the head coach
in Orlando. Cleveland. then Detroit.

314
00:13:02.531 --> 00:13:03.949
Okay. where is he now?

315
00:13:04.033 --> 00:13:08.037
According to Wikipedia.
he currently resides in Anaheim.

316
00:13:09.121 --> 00:13:11.665
I wanna meet with him.
so send him the plane.

317
00:13:12.458 --> 00:13:13.709
It's a 45-minute drive.

318
00:13:13.793 --> 00:13:15.419
-Anaheim?
-Yeah.

319
00:13:15.503 --> 00:13:16.837
Then where am I thinking?

320
00:13:17.421 --> 00:13:18.297
I have no idea.

321
00:13:19.131 --> 00:13:22.635
♪ Put your hands in the air
Put your hands in the air ♪

322
00:13:22.718 --> 00:13:24.261
[Travis] Hey. are you guys decent?

323
00:13:24.345 --> 00:13:26.222
Because I got a VIP guest
about to come in.

324
00:13:26.305 --> 00:13:29.183
Oh. man. I can't be doing no more selfies
with your sponsor.

325
00:13:29.266 --> 00:13:31.685
-It's not Dennis. dude. It's a girl.
-[all jeering].

326
00:13:31.769 --> 00:13:34.563
Okay. so put your clothes on. perverts.

327
00:13:34.647 --> 00:13:38.901
And allow me to introduce
my new bae. Zoé Debay.

328
00:13:38.984 --> 00:13:40.152
[all exclaiming]

329
00:13:40.236 --> 00:13:41.111
Hey. everyone.

330
00:13:41.195 --> 00:13:42.321
Ah. who is this woman?

331
00:13:42.905 --> 00:13:46.575
Benson. how do you not know Zoé Debay?
She had her own kids' show.

332
00:13:46.659 --> 00:13:50.287
Oh. I… I didn't watch a lot of TV
in Nigeria. I was popular.

333
00:13:50.371 --> 00:13:52.790
It was called Triple Trouble.
She played triplets.

334
00:13:52.873 --> 00:13:55.668
-Nice to meet you. Zoé.
-Miss Debay. big fan.

335
00:13:55.751 --> 00:13:57.127
It's an honor to meet you.

336
00:13:57.211 --> 00:13:58.671
[Zoé] I'm a big Waves fan.

337
00:13:58.754 --> 00:14:03.092
Y'all were robbed last year. but I know
you're getting that ring this year.

338
00:14:03.175 --> 00:14:05.219
-Yeah!
-[excited chatter]

339
00:14:05.302 --> 00:14:07.096
All right. enough.

340
00:14:07.179 --> 00:14:08.848
Zoé. the tour continues.

341
00:14:08.931 --> 00:14:10.766
Next up. HR and payroll.

342
00:14:10.850 --> 00:14:12.309
[hopeful music playing]

343
00:14:12.393 --> 00:14:13.686
Oof!

344
00:14:16.814 --> 00:14:20.234
Can we hurry up? I have a pickleball match
in an hour with Stamos.

345
00:14:20.317 --> 00:14:24.321
-Oh. you made the connection. Nice.
-Guy covers the court like a gazelle.

346
00:14:24.405 --> 00:14:26.907
Danny finds out we're jerking off
another coach. he's gonna be pissed.

347
00:14:26.991 --> 00:14:28.033
and that's gonna be on you.

348
00:14:28.117 --> 00:14:31.203
Yeah. but I will say
Norm would be a lot cheaper than Danny.

349
00:14:31.287 --> 00:14:34.206
Yes. I just wanna exhaust
all possibilities.

350
00:14:34.290 --> 00:14:37.001
Jackie. you can bring Norm in now.

351
00:14:37.084 --> 00:14:39.253
He fell asleep in reception.
Should I wake him up?

352
00:14:39.837 --> 00:14:42.423
-No. he's… he's probably meditating.
-He was snoring.

353
00:14:42.506 --> 00:14:44.842
-Hmm.
-Jackie. just bring him in. please.

354
00:14:47.553 --> 00:14:50.055
Well. it's good
to see you kids again. huh?

355
00:14:50.139 --> 00:14:51.599
It's been a long time.

356
00:14:52.266 --> 00:14:56.145
All right. let's see.
Cam. glad to hear you're off of drugs.

357
00:14:56.228 --> 00:14:57.479
Yeah. that's a good call.

358
00:14:57.563 --> 00:15:00.733
Isla. Hey.
you're finally getting married. good.

359
00:15:00.816 --> 00:15:03.485
Yeah. you were single a long time.
so that's good.

360
00:15:03.569 --> 00:15:06.405
Ness. Asian wife. that's progress.

361
00:15:06.488 --> 00:15:09.700
And Sandy. you're. uh… gay.

362
00:15:10.659 --> 00:15:11.535
Yes.

363
00:15:11.619 --> 00:15:15.122
Yeah. Norm.
you've got a really impressive résumé.

364
00:15:15.205 --> 00:15:18.083
You have a .605 career winning percentage.

365
00:15:18.167 --> 00:15:20.669
five division titles
with three different teams.

366
00:15:20.753 --> 00:15:23.005
I mean. what have you
been up to these last years?

367
00:15:23.088 --> 00:15:25.591
Well. I got a condo in Anaheim.

368
00:15:25.674 --> 00:15:29.511
Yeah. right next to a Peet's Coffee shop.
so I go there every day.

369
00:15:30.721 --> 00:15:31.847
Anything else?

370
00:15:31.931 --> 00:15:34.725
I have a daughter. She lives in Boston.
doesn't talk to me anymore.

371
00:15:34.808 --> 00:15:36.352
Her husband. he doesn't work.

372
00:15:36.435 --> 00:15:40.272
and I refuse to call him
a "full-time dad."

373
00:15:40.356 --> 00:15:42.524
He wears a fedora.
Get the fuck out of here.

374
00:15:44.151 --> 00:15:49.740
Um. Norm. this last year in Detroit.
uh. do you want to tell us what happened?

375
00:15:49.823 --> 00:15:53.619
Well. let's just say I. uh.
I was dealing with some personal stuff.

376
00:15:54.370 --> 00:15:57.414
-Would you care to elaborate on that?
-No.

377
00:15:58.332 --> 00:16:01.377
We don't need to focus on the past.
Let's talk about the future.

378
00:16:01.460 --> 00:16:03.837
Norm. what do you think
about the state of our team?

379
00:16:03.921 --> 00:16:07.007
Yeah. what would you do
to. say. maximize player efficiency

380
00:16:07.091 --> 00:16:09.134
or improve our EFG?

381
00:16:09.218 --> 00:16:11.345
Well. I don't know
what any of that shit means.

382
00:16:11.428 --> 00:16:13.138
but what I'd say about your team…

383
00:16:13.222 --> 00:16:15.599
Okay. so Marcus.
you're paying him too much money.

384
00:16:15.683 --> 00:16:18.143
Travis holds onto the ball too damn long.

385
00:16:18.227 --> 00:16:21.814
And. oh well… Oh no. well.
you gave him too many corner threes.

386
00:16:21.897 --> 00:16:24.024
Yeah. Very. very sloppy.

387
00:16:24.108 --> 00:16:27.027
-Did we do anything right?
-Uh… let's see.

388
00:16:27.945 --> 00:16:30.072
Jay. great coach.

389
00:16:30.698 --> 00:16:32.032
I don't why you let him go.

390
00:16:32.116 --> 00:16:36.620
Oh. this is where my passwords are.
Now I can get back into my apps.

391
00:16:37.371 --> 00:16:39.289
I gotta buy some compression socks.

392
00:16:40.249 --> 00:16:43.794
Norm. it was great to catch up.
Thank you for coming in.

393
00:16:44.920 --> 00:16:47.965
Okay. all right.
Well. I gotta go anyway. I'm at a meter.

394
00:16:48.048 --> 00:16:50.009
I didn't put any money in
because I roll the dice.

395
00:16:50.092 --> 00:16:52.011
If you don't mind.
what's the deal with the snacks?

396
00:16:52.094 --> 00:16:54.555
-Oh. go ahead. Go ahead. help yourself.
-Really? Okay.

397
00:16:54.638 --> 00:16:56.724
This will go good with my coffee.

398
00:16:56.807 --> 00:16:59.018
-I'm a dunker.
-Just take 'em. Norm. Thanks for coming.

399
00:16:59.101 --> 00:17:00.811
-Okay. thank you.
-[Isla] Bye. Norm.

400
00:17:00.894 --> 00:17:02.688
-All right.
-Can we hire Danny now.

401
00:17:02.771 --> 00:17:05.607
or are there other befuddled. broken men
you'd like to speak to?

402
00:17:05.691 --> 00:17:07.818
All right. fine. We'll go with Danny.

403
00:17:08.402 --> 00:17:09.945
-Can I go?
-[Isla] Yep.

404
00:17:10.029 --> 00:17:11.488
Monica. call Stamos!

405
00:17:15.451 --> 00:17:16.326
Whoo!

406
00:17:17.036 --> 00:17:18.579
Where did Dollar Store Dyson go?

407
00:17:18.662 --> 00:17:19.997
I am feeling this.

408
00:17:20.080 --> 00:17:20.956
As you should.

409
00:17:21.040 --> 00:17:23.042
I might get a couple of these
while I'm here.

410
00:17:24.209 --> 00:17:27.504
-Oh my God. is that in pesos?
-Don't worry about the price.

411
00:17:27.588 --> 00:17:30.382
-Are you buying?
-No. Just don't worry about the price.

412
00:17:31.050 --> 00:17:33.385
I'm gonna go grab you some belts.
Chill here.

413
00:17:33.469 --> 00:17:35.596
Don't be asking anyone
about a bargain bin.

414
00:17:39.058 --> 00:17:41.435
[Zoé] Wow. looking good.

415
00:17:41.518 --> 00:17:43.896
-Oh. hey. Zoé. What are you doing here?
-[chuckles]

416
00:17:43.979 --> 00:17:45.981
Just shopping.
You wanna know something crazy?

417
00:17:46.065 --> 00:17:49.485
I actually grew up
the biggest Long Beach Raccoons fan.

418
00:17:49.568 --> 00:17:51.737
-Really? [laughs]
-Yeah. we couldn't afford Waves seats.

419
00:17:51.820 --> 00:17:55.532
The D-league gave free tickets to my
church. so we went to Raccoons games.

420
00:17:55.616 --> 00:17:57.826
-Oh. you've been to The Cage?
-Like a thousand times.

421
00:17:57.910 --> 00:17:59.328
I saw you play once.

422
00:17:59.411 --> 00:18:02.539
You were on fire.
but they had to stop the game at halftime

423
00:18:02.623 --> 00:18:04.750
because the team forgot
to pay the electric bill.

424
00:18:04.833 --> 00:18:06.710
Yeah. the owner was a real bad gambler.

425
00:18:06.794 --> 00:18:08.337
[chuckles] We gotta take a pic.

426
00:18:08.420 --> 00:18:11.006
-My dad'll freak when I tell him we met.
-Let's do it.

427
00:18:11.924 --> 00:18:13.175
-[camera clicks]
-[Zoé chuckles]

428
00:18:13.258 --> 00:18:16.095
Give me your phone
so I can share it. [chuckles]

429
00:18:16.178 --> 00:18:19.932
Okay. There. now you have my number.
So. are you gonna get this suit?

430
00:18:20.808 --> 00:18:24.228
[sighs deeply] I don't know.
I'm worried it's not nice enough.

431
00:18:24.812 --> 00:18:26.480
Mm. Well. that's too bad.

432
00:18:27.272 --> 00:18:28.273
You wear it well.

433
00:18:28.357 --> 00:18:29.483
[laughs]

434
00:18:29.566 --> 00:18:31.276
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

435
00:18:31.360 --> 00:18:33.862
-So what are you doing after this?
-[Zoé] Just some shopping.

436
00:18:33.946 --> 00:18:36.949
Then I have a meeting later
about this movie my agent wants me to do.

437
00:18:37.032 --> 00:18:38.784
[Dyson] Wow. that is so cool.

438
00:18:39.284 --> 00:18:40.869
[groovy music playing]

439
00:18:42.830 --> 00:18:44.039
[music fades]

440
00:18:44.123 --> 00:18:46.291
Isla. I have Danny Pierce's agent.
line two.

441
00:18:46.375 --> 00:18:50.420
Hey. Norm left this in my office.
Oh. sorry. I mean conference room.

442
00:18:52.297 --> 00:18:53.674
[suspenseful music playing]

443
00:18:53.757 --> 00:18:54.633
Holy shit.

444
00:18:55.342 --> 00:18:57.010
Isla. Danny's agent holding.

445
00:18:58.679 --> 00:19:00.514
Yeah. tell him I'll call him back.

446
00:19:00.597 --> 00:19:02.141
[music continues]

447
00:19:08.897 --> 00:19:13.152
Hi. I'm looking for
a grouchy. older gentleman.

448
00:19:15.571 --> 00:19:16.905
Thank you.

449
00:19:20.242 --> 00:19:22.411
-Norm. Oh!
-Oh. shit!

450
00:19:23.704 --> 00:19:24.830
You can't do that.

451
00:19:24.913 --> 00:19:27.666
You can't sneak up on somebody like that.
I almost had a heart attack.

452
00:19:27.749 --> 00:19:28.917
I didn't sneak up on you.

453
00:19:29.001 --> 00:19:32.045
I gently tapped you
on the shoulder and lightly said. "Norm."

454
00:19:32.129 --> 00:19:35.257
[spluttering] I didn't know where
it was coming from. It was like a ghost.

455
00:19:35.340 --> 00:19:36.842
-Can I… Can I just sit down?
-Yeah.

456
00:19:37.968 --> 00:19:40.762
-What are you doing here?
-I am here to yell at you.

457
00:19:41.346 --> 00:19:44.099
I went to bat for you.
That interview was terrible.

458
00:19:44.183 --> 00:19:47.019
Your answers were all bad.
and honestly. you were kind of rude.

459
00:19:47.102 --> 00:19:50.397
Wait a minute. Is this about the snacks?
Because all of you said I could have them.

460
00:19:50.480 --> 00:19:53.775
You took everything.
an entire grocery bag of snacks.

461
00:19:54.651 --> 00:19:55.777
[sighs]

462
00:19:56.361 --> 00:19:59.615
Norm. what happened in Detroit?

463
00:20:00.949 --> 00:20:04.077
And if I was to hire you. how would I know
that wouldn't happen again?

464
00:20:06.955 --> 00:20:09.708
Well. I don't think my wife can die twice.

465
00:20:09.791 --> 00:20:11.627
[sad music playing]

466
00:20:15.714 --> 00:20:19.843
Yeah. my wife Andrea passed away
from ovarian cancer

467
00:20:19.927 --> 00:20:21.345
the last season that I coached.

468
00:20:22.387 --> 00:20:23.931
I'm so sorry. I…

469
00:20:27.935 --> 00:20:29.436
She got diagnosed

470
00:20:30.729 --> 00:20:35.150
and suddenly basketball became
very unimportant.

471
00:20:36.944 --> 00:20:40.113
Then when she passed. I kind of shut down.

472
00:20:41.698 --> 00:20:42.908
Started hanging out here.

473
00:20:45.619 --> 00:20:46.828
That's really tough.

474
00:20:46.912 --> 00:20:48.830
No. it's actually pretty nice

475
00:20:48.914 --> 00:20:51.500
because they gave me
my own copy of the bathroom key

476
00:20:51.583 --> 00:20:53.585
so I don't have to keep going up
and asking for it.

477
00:20:53.669 --> 00:20:55.879
[keys clanging]

478
00:20:55.963 --> 00:20:57.381
You know. believe it or not.

479
00:20:58.715 --> 00:21:02.970
that meeting was the first time
I talked to other people in a while.

480
00:21:04.471 --> 00:21:05.347
I believe it.

481
00:21:05.430 --> 00:21:06.682
[Norm chuckles]

482
00:21:07.808 --> 00:21:10.269
-You left your notebook.
-Oh. Oh. I left it?

483
00:21:11.103 --> 00:21:12.771
-Hmm.
-I may have taken a peek.

484
00:21:13.355 --> 00:21:16.191
You broke down all
of our defensive sets in the playoffs

485
00:21:16.275 --> 00:21:19.820
and basically reverse engineered them
for a new scheme.

486
00:21:19.903 --> 00:21:22.489
Yeah. well. I watched
every Waves game last season.

487
00:21:22.572 --> 00:21:25.033
So. you don't think
we should move to a man-to-man defense?

488
00:21:25.117 --> 00:21:27.452
No. no. You don't throw out
a system that works.

489
00:21:27.536 --> 00:21:30.622
You just shift the guard
to the high triangle with Marcus and Bugg.

490
00:21:30.706 --> 00:21:32.666
that's gonna shrink the floor on defense.

491
00:21:32.749 --> 00:21:34.710
Teams are gonna shoot 8% worse from deep.

492
00:21:34.793 --> 00:21:39.006
This way. Marcus doesn't have to sprint
like he's 25. It's too much wear and tear.

493
00:21:41.425 --> 00:21:42.968
No. you got a good team.

494
00:21:43.969 --> 00:21:44.803
Isla.

495
00:21:45.804 --> 00:21:48.598
And. uh. more importantly.

496
00:21:50.058 --> 00:21:51.101
they got you.

497
00:21:54.896 --> 00:21:57.274
I have a feeling
it wasn't a mistake you left this behind.

498
00:21:57.899 --> 00:22:00.610
Now give me your whisk.
It's a long drive home.

499
00:22:01.570 --> 00:22:04.406
-Yeah. thanks.
-You gotta jiggle the handle.

500
00:22:04.489 --> 00:22:06.491
[R&B music playing]

501
00:22:07.909 --> 00:22:09.411
Yo. D. hold up.

502
00:22:09.494 --> 00:22:11.413
-Yo.
-I wanna talk to you about something.

503
00:22:11.496 --> 00:22:12.748
Bro. I gotta talk to you too.

504
00:22:12.831 --> 00:22:15.834
I spent so much money on this suit.
I can't afford shoes.

505
00:22:15.917 --> 00:22:18.170
-Are high-tops okay?
-You… you're buying shoes.

506
00:22:18.253 --> 00:22:19.171
But…

507
00:22:19.254 --> 00:22:20.255
Ain't about that.

508
00:22:21.089 --> 00:22:22.507
I saw you sweating Zoé.

509
00:22:23.133 --> 00:22:25.802
